Date:  0/0/1926
Source:  Transport Workers' Song Book
Author:
Vol / Page:  24
Edition:
Quote:  I don't stand up to look for work, I come down to make a start; / For I'm classed among the `ringers', and from others stand apart. / Whilst on the job I'm set for life, and I'm doing well I vow. / For I've got the boss behind me, So I want no Union now.
